text: Went Tokyo Taste, ordered chicken katsu omucurry don and Park and Salmon Sumiyaki don. The curry taste good, they torch the salmon n pork well. Just that if the pork could be less fatty, the taste will be awesome.

I ordered the pork katsu don from the japanese store. Comes with miso soup and salad for $12.90.

Pork meat was tough.
Katsu was not crispy.
Whole dish lacks flavour.

Nice atmosphere, nicely renovated.  Tried the chicken cutlet, very satisfied, drinks stall is more like a bar counter....  beers , wines, bottles
beers in bucket, bubble teas.  Food court / restaurant in day, pub at night maybe.

Nice environment, ordered from the Chicken rice store. The accompanying soup not bad, the rice ok. The chicken tender but a little lack flavor. The chilli get the kick which is nice, but it's too SOUR. Too much vinegar, taken over the chicken rice flavour totally. Otherwise ok.

It's a food court place, there's only 6 stalls. Coming here at around 8.45pm, most of the stalls are shutting down. Only  the you tiao / soya bean stalls (I find the price reasonable) and China zhi cha stall available.
